abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump has days to decide whether to impose tariffs on nearly $160 billion in Chinese consumer goods just weeks before Christmas, a move that could be unwelcome in both the United States and China.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump has days to decide whether to impose tariffs on nearly $160 billion in Chinese consumer goods just weeks before Christmas, a move that could be unwelcome in both the United States and China.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump has days to decide whether to impose tariffs on nearly $160 billion in Chinese consumer goods just weeks before Christmas, a move that could be unwelcome in both the United States and China.
headline_main: Focus Squarely on Trump as Dec 15 Tariffs Loom in US-China Trade War
headline_print_headline: Focus Squarely on Trump as Dec 15 Tariffs Loom in US-China Trade War

abstract: Shares of the world’s largest oil company rose 10 percent during their market debut. The offering is expected to set a record.

abstract: There are a lot of different ways to build walls.
snippet: There are a lot of different ways to build walls.
lead_paragraph: Donald Trump has done everything within his power to activate racial and ethnic animosity in this country. His main targets are immigrants, who are often greeted with rank hatred. But it’s a mistake to think that Trump started all this, even as he’s taking full advantage of the opportunities animosity has unleashed. He’s riding a wave.

headline_main: Trump Has a Gift for Tearing Us Apart

abstract: The presidential candidates need to stop demurring and fully reject Trump’s approach.
snippet: The presidential candidates need to stop demurring and fully reject Trump’s approach.
lead_paragraph: When it comes to trade policy with China, the Democratic presidential candidates face a conundrum. They don’t want to sign onto President Trump’s endless, chaotic, pain-over-gain trade war, yet they don’t want to appear weak or appeasing of China’s trade practices.

headline_main: Donald Trump, Jersey City, New York Yankees: Your Wednesday Briefing

abstract: Unable to form a government after two elections, the deeply polarized country will return to the polls for a third time in less than a year.
snippet: Unable to form a government after two elections, the deeply polarized country will return to the polls for a third time in less than a year.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — Having failed to form a government after two elections, Israel barreled toward a record third on Wednesday, extending the political deadlock that has paralyzed the country for nearly a year and assuring at least three more months of bitter, divisive campaigning and government dysfunction.

abstract: Research shows that Generation Z is the first in which women are more likely than their male peers to be engaged in politics. Here’s what some of them told us.
